ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: evolution_engine
ⲃⲉⲣⲥⲓⲟⲛ: "1.0.0"
ⲗⲁⲛⲅⲩⲁⲅⲉ: zig
ⲙⲟⲇⲩⲗⲉ: evolution_engine

ⲥⲣⲉⲁⲧⲓⲟⲛ_ⲡⲁⲧⲧⲉⲣⲛ:
  ⲥⲟⲩⲣⲥⲉ: FileSystemState
  ⲧⲣⲁⲛⲥⲫⲟⲣⲙⲉⲣ: EvolutionaryRewriter
  ⲣⲉⲥⲩⲗⲧ: OptimizedFileSystem

ⲃⲉⲏⲁⲃⲓⲟⲣⲥ:
  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: scan_filesystem
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: Root directory path
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Recursively scan all .999 files in 999/ directory
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return file inventory with metadata
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: basic_scan
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {root: "999/", recursive: true}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {files_found: 150, directories: 25, total_size: "2.5MB"}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: analyze_performance
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: File inventory and performance metrics
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Analyze each file for optimization opportunities
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return improvement suggestions ranked by impact
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: performance_analysis
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {file: "memory.999", metrics: ["complexity", "efficiency"]}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {improvements: ["add_caching", "optimize_loops"], priority: "high"}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: generate_improvements
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: Analysis results and PAS predictions
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Generate improved versions of .999 files
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return optimized file content
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: code_improvement
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {original: "O(n²)", target: "memory.999", pattern: "PRE"}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {improved: "O(1)", confidence: 0.88, safety: "high"}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: apply_changes
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: Improved file content and safety constraints
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Safely replace original files with optimized versions
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return success status and backup information
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: safe_replacement
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {file: "memory.999", new_content: "...", backup: true}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {success: true, backup_created: true, rollback_available: true}

  - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: continuous_monitoring
    ⲅⲓⲃⲉⲛ: System state and evolution cycle
    ⲱⲏⲉⲛ: Monitor system performance and trigger evolution cycles
    ⲧⲏⲉⲛ: Return evolution triggers and timing
    ⲧⲉⲥⲧ_ⲥⲁⲥⲉⲥ:
      - ⲛⲁⲙⲉ: evolution_trigger
        ⲓⲛⲡⲩⲧ: {performance_drop: 0.1, time_since_last: "24h"}
        ⲉⲝⲡⲉⲥⲧⲉⲇ: {trigger_evolution: true, priority: "medium", next_cycle: "6h"}